                <h1>Understanding the Vietnam War: Key Facts and Insights</h1>
                <p>The Vietnam War, lasting from 1955 to 1975, was a controversial conflict between North Vietnam and South Vietnam, supported by the USA. It was marked by guerilla warfare, heavy casualties, and deep societal divisions. The war significantly influenced American culture, policy, and ultimately led to the withdrawal of U.S. troops, leaving a lasting legacy.</p>
